Working address: Pakxan factory and Atapu factory in Laos.
Scale: Each factory has more than 500 workers. Total more than 1500 workers at 3 factories.
a. Human Resources
- Managing the supply of human resources services of the Company.
- Organizing and planning human resources, staffing the whole factory; design job descriptions, personnel standards, capacity profiles; Maintaining and improving policies, procedures and regulations on human resources; rules, norms, programs for developing company culture.
Recruitment:
ü Planning, recruitment organizations to meet the requirements of the units;
ü Directly recruiting Lao and Vietnamese workers to factories;
ü Develop & improve the recruitment, training and retiring processes;
ü Develop recruitment regulations for each factory;
- Training for integration and intensive training planning:
Guide construction units: job descriptions; capacity framework, personnel standards; Identify training needs and summarize training needs of units;
- Organize the construction of training programs for training units & materials;
- Organize training programs; integration training for new employees joining the Company;
- Develop promotion path and staff development policy.
- Manage recruiting budgets, train & evaluate recruitment efficiency; effective training; Managing personnel fluctuations, analyzing and proposing solutions to align employees;
- Directing the formulation of salary scales and payrolls and managing how to pay employees.
- Managing social insurance payment activities, declaring personal income tax by month, quarter and year.
